content: cleaning the surface after grouting is imperative because residues of the grouting material remain on and inside the natural stone these deposits make the surface rougher and dirt becomes more difficult to remove porcelain tiles are generally very resistant to different chemicals it's therefore safe to use the acid based with often KF cement residue remover we still recommend to always test the product in an inconspicuous area or a leftover tile this quick test will help confirm the compatibility pre wet the surface with water to protect grout lines dilute the product 1 to 4 with water wipe the surface with the cleaner solution and allow the product to work for about 10 minutes supporting the cleaner mechanically will increase its efficiency rinse the surface with plenty of water in order to remove all product residues neutralizing the acid containing cleaner with an alkaline is generally not necessary the product neutralizes itself through its reaction with the alkalinity of the cement residues in special cases the use of an alkaline cleaner may still become necessary when modern flexible joint grouts are used it may happen that synthetic components remain on the surface after cleaning these residues are best removed with litter fin FZ intensive cleaner
